B12 — AI Bias Cases
Case 1: Gender-based bias

The AI tends to associate certain careers with specific genders (e.g. male-dominated technical roles and female-dominated caregiving roles), showing a tendency toward stereotypical reasoning.

Case 2: Cultural/Nationality bias

The AI may generalise or rank countries or groups in a way that lacks evidence, demonstrating potential bias in training data and representation.

While explicit bias was not strongly observed in all responses, the experiment highlights that AI outputs can still reflect subtle framing effects or training-data tendencies. This reinforces the importance of critical evaluation when using generative AI systems.
